00:21:39.366 --> 00:21:40.500
Very nice.

00:21:44.266 --> 00:21:45.866
Wow, what a great drive.

00:21:49.966 --> 00:21:54.766
The AV stack drives very much like a human,

00:21:54.766 --> 00:21:57.600
that imitates a human and generalizes incredibly

00:21:57.600 --> 00:21:59.000
to all these different scenarios.

00:21:59.200 --> 00:22:01.100
And the classical AV stack

00:22:01.100 --> 00:22:02.900
gives us the safety guardrails

00:22:02.900 --> 00:22:05.333
that have been fine-tuned and tested,

00:22:05.500 --> 00:22:07.566
and with all of the engineering rules

00:22:07.566 --> 00:22:08.500
that have been put into it,

00:22:08.500 --> 00:22:10.200
gives us incredible safety.

00:22:10.300 --> 00:22:12.700
And so now when we were driving,

00:22:12.700 --> 00:22:14.200
the two of us were just talking,

00:22:14.500 --> 00:22:17.066
enjoying San Francisco, and it was just incredible.

00:22:17.066 --> 00:22:20.000
This is the way transportation should be.

00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:21.633
That's right— a hundred percent comfortable,

00:22:21.633 --> 00:22:22.800
a hundred percent confident,

00:22:22.800 --> 00:22:26.000
you know, and completely revolutionary.

